14.02 | Principles of Macroeconomics | http://ocw.mit.edu/courses/economics/14-02-principles-of-macroeconomics-spring-2014 | level:Undergraduate instructors:Francesco Giavazzi term:Spring 2014 features:Selected lecture notes, Assignments and solutions, Exams and solutions textbook:Macroeconomics (Blanchard, Olivier; Johnson, David R.) description:Provides an overview of macroeconomic issues: the determination of output, employment, unemployment, interest rates, and inflation. Monetary and fiscal policies are discussed. Important current policy debates such as the sub-prime crisis, social security, the public debt, and international economic issues are critically explored. Introduces basic models of macroeconomics and illustrates principles with the experience of the US and foreign economies. Taught in two formats - lecture/recitation and recitation only - each with 3 sessions per week. Same content and exams. 
