14.16 | Strategy and Information | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=14.16 Strategy and Information | instructors:M. Manea  prereq:14.12 description:Begins with a rigorous overview of the main equilbrium concepts for non-cooperative games in normal and extensive form, with complete or incomplete information. Defines and explores properties of iterated dominance, rationalizability, Nash equilibrium, subgame perfection, perfect Bayesian equilibrium, and sequential, perfect and proper equilibria. Introduces solution concepts for cooperative games and studies non-cooperative implementations. Other topics include matching and allocation problems, auctions and mechanism design, and reputation. Bargaining and networks are recurring themes. 
