14.740 | Foundations of Development Policy | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=14.740 Foundations of Development Policy | instructors:E. Duflo, B. Olken  prereq:14.30 14.01 description:Explores the foundations of policy making in developing countries. Goal is to spell out various policy options and to quantify the trade-offs between them. Special emphasis on education, health, gender, fertility, adoption of technological innovation, and the markets for land, credit, and labor.  Students taking the graduate version complete additional assignments. 
14.75 | Political Economy and Economic Development | http://ocw.mit.edu/courses/economics/14-75-political-economy-and-economic-development-fall-2012 | level:Undergraduate instructors:Benjamin Olken term:Fall 2012 features:Selected lecture notes, Assignments (no solutions) textbook:Analyzing Politics: Rationality, Behavior, and Instititutions (Bonchek, Mark S.; Shepsle, Kenneth A.) prereq:14.30 14.01 description:Explores the relationship between political institutions and economic development, covering key theoretical issues as well as recent empirical evidence. Topics include corruption, democracy, dictatorship, and war. Discusses not just what we know on these topics, but how we know it, covering how to craft a good empirical study or field experiment and how to discriminate between reliable and unreliable evidence. 
